   (ART ADV: Photo and graphic are being sent to NYT photo/graphics
clients.)
</P>
<P>
   QWEST-USWEST (Undated) _ As the smoke clears from the
communications industry's latest takeover battleground, the
companies that recently fired so many billion-dollar salvos _
Global Crossing, Frontier, Qwest and US West _ have left unresolved
issues scattered like so many spent cartridges. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   MP3-MARKETPLACE (Palo Alto, Calif.) _ The bands cracking the top
10 music chart this week are Red Delicious and the Streaming Geeks.
No, the hit list is not the Billboard Top 40, but one from Mp3.com,
an unconventional force in the music industry that is scheduled to
make an initial public offering this week. By Matt Richtel.
</P>
<P>
   DEALS-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ More agencies and agency companies
are agreeing to deals to sell full or partial control to larger
firms, as the acquisition boom remaking Madison Avenue continues.
By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
