<HEADLINE>
BORGES' MAID SAVED HIM FROM LONELINESS 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (This has already moved to clients of Tomas Eloy Martinez'
biweekly column. To publish it as a ``separate buy'' article, it
must be purchased _ the rate is not prohibitive _ from one of these
New York Times Syndicate sales representatives: 
 &HT;    (--U.S. and Canada: DEBRA WEYDERT in New Jersey at
1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697. 
 &HT;    (--Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942. 
 &HT;    (--Latin America: OLIVIA VASQUEZ in Los Angeles, 310-798-0970;
fax, 310-798-7338.) 
 &HT;    
 By TOMAS ELOY MARTINEZ  
 c.1999 New York Times Special Features  
<TEXT>
<P>
   History has been stingy up to now with Fani Uveda, the woman who
