sergeant at Scotland Yard.
 &HT;    Myatt, 50, sturdily built with the toughened hands of a laborer,
nodded with resigned expectancy and invited the policemen inside
for tea. Then he asked if could walk his son to the bus.
 &HT;    While he did, the officers ransacked the house. Upon returning,
Myatt stood in the studio with Searle, surveying the chaos.
 &HT;    ``Do you like this one?'' Myatt asked, pointing to a competent
if undistinguished drawing of his son.
 &HT;    Searle nodded sympathetically, but was amazed by what looked to
be paintings by Giacometti, Chagall, Braque and Dubuffet hanging
about the room. Drawing pads lying around showed sketched studies
for works by Giacometti, Le Corbusier and Ben Nicholson.
 &HT;    Myatt confessed on the spot to having drawn and painted what the
police later said were about 200 forgeries in the styles of nine
