<P>
   Breast-feeding protects babies from cancer, but no one knows
quite how. So when biologists in Catharina Svanborg's lab saw
cancer cells commit suicide when placed in mother's milk, they knew
they were onto something big. Peter Radetsy, a contributing editor
to Discover magazine, reports.
</P>
<P>
   slugged: BC-BREAST-MILK-CANCER-KILLER-NYTSF. Sent to category
codes ``a'' general news and ``l'' lifestyle news.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE PHYSICS OF ... TAPE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; ONE COLOR SLIDE IS AVAILABLE FREE &QL; 
 &UR; (1,100 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By ROBERT KUNZIG &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Ever wonder how Post-it notes work? How about Scotch tape? We
live in an age when everything from space-shuttle engines to
disposable diapers are strewn with adhesives. Yet we still don't
know exactly what makes them stick. Or do we? A couple of French
physicists think the answer lies in bubbles. Robert Kunzig, the
European Editor of Discover magazine, reports.
</P>
<P>
   slugged: BC-MYSTERY-OF-TAPE-NYTSF. Sent to category codes ``a''
general news and ``l'' lifestyle news.
</P>
