 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (UNDATED) - Kevin W. Mannoia is the newly elected president of
the National Association of Evangelicals. He took office in July
after finishing his term as the bishop of the Free Methodist Church
of North America.
</P>
<P>
   The NAE represents more than 49 evangelical denominations with
about 43,000 congregations in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Mannoia, 43, has been a church planter for the Free Methodist
Church denomination and a conference superintendent for Free
Methodist churches in Texas and California. He has been a pastor,
author and college teacher. He is married and has three children.
</P>
