<HEADLINE>
THE REV. JIMMY CREECH 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (UNDATED) - Jimmy Creech is an ordained elder in the United
Methodist Church on voluntary leave of absence from the Nebraska
Annual Conference. In March 1998, he was acquitted in a church
trial on a charge of violating the Order and Discipline of the
United Methodist Church when he celebrated a covenant ceremony for
two women in September of 1997.
</P>
<P>
   The Nebraska bishop did not allow him to continue as senior
pastor of First United Methodist Church, Omaha. The church judicial
process is formally underway for another same-sex union that he
celebrated in April.
</P>
<P>
   Creech, 54, writes and speaks about lesbian and gay persecution
by the Christian church. He is married and has two children.
</P>
