<SLUG> BC-GAYSCRIPTURE-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INTERPRETATIONS OF THE SCRIPTURES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (UNDATED) - For mainline Protestants, the debate over the
acceptance and the roles of gays and lesbians in the church - from
the blessing of same-sex unions to the ordination of non-celibate
gay pastors - is growing increasingly divisive. At the heart of the
debate are six scriptures. The Arizona Republic asked two
nationally known theologians for their interpretations of those
verses. The scriptures are from the New International Version of
the Bible. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
``Before they had gone to bed, all the men from every part of the
city of Sodom - both young and old - surrounded the house. They
called to Lot, `Where are the men who came to you tonight? Bring
them out to us so that we can have sex with them.' Lot went outside
to meet them and shut the door behind him and said, `No, my
friends. Don't do this wicked thing. Look, I have two daughters who
have never slept with a man.' '' - Genesis 19:5-8 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
``Do not lie with a man as one lies with a woman; that is
detestable.'' - Leviticus 18:22 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
``If a man lies with a man as one lies with a woman, both of them
have done what is detestable. They must be put to death; their
blood will be on their own heads.'' - Leviticus 20:13 &QL; 
 &QL; 
``Because of this, God gave them over to shameful lusts. Even their
women exchanged natural relations for unnatural ones. In the same
way, the men also abandoned natural relations with women and were
inflamed with lust for one another. Men committed indecent acts
with other men, and received in themselves the due penalty for
their perversion.'' - Romans 1:26-27 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
``Do you not know that the wicked will not inherit the kingdom of
God? Do not be deceived: Neither the sexually immoral nor idolaters
nor adulterers nor male prostitutes nor homosexual offenders nor
thieves nor the greedy nor drunkards nor slanderers nor swindlers
will inherit the kingdom of God.'' - 1 Corinthians 6:9-10  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
``We also know that law is made not for good men but for
lawbreakers and rebels, the ungodly and sinful, the unholy and
irreligious, for those who kill their fathers or mothers, for
murderers, for adulterers and perverts, for slave traders and liars
and perjurers - and for whatever else is contrary to the sound
doctrine that conforms to the glorious gospel of the blessed God,
which he entrusted to me.'' - 1 Timothy 1:9-11 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
