   What a deal: Andorra gives its citizens free postage.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mailbag: Leigh B. Smith of Vineyard Haven, Mass. writes that the
Norwegian Majesty wasn't the only cruise ship diverted from Bermuda
recently because of the possibility of adverse weather. The
Celebrity ships Zenith and Horizon, she writes, spent June 18
anchored off Martha's Vineyard. ``Great for me as my friends . . .
were aboard the Zenith for a 50th anniversary cruise. My husband
and I were able to toast them with champagne and spend anniversary
time with them at our Vineyard home!'' The ship did get to spend 2
1/2 days in Bermuda before the decision was made to leave.
</P>
