<P>
   PAGE INCLUDES FIVE COLOR PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   VIRTUAL VIOLENCE: The Columbine High killings have prompted
lawsuits against the makers of Doom and cries for a government
crackdown on violent video games. But most parents are probably
unaware that Doom is kid stuff compared with the games that are
coming out now. (Includes one 4-column color photograph of teen
playing a video game and a 2-column color detail photo of a warning
label on a video game.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECH BRIEFS: The Discovery Channel's Web site and the
American Museum of Natural History have collaborated on a site that
explores the Earth. (Includes 18-pica color photo from Web site.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECHNOBUDDY: Many people in the news industry worry that
the Web and all the news sites there have turned the newspaper into
a dinosaur, doddering on its last legs, dying slowly. There's
little chance of that. (Includes 1 column color sig of columnist.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: GADGETS: Embarrassed when you're required to show your
passport or student ID because you despise that goofy photo? Here's
help. Sony has come up with a Digital Passport Photo System that
lets you preview and pick your preferred passport photo before it's
printed. (Includes 18-pica color photo of photo system.)
</P>
