   PROTESTER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Her friends and supporters put on their
protest T-shirts, carried ``Prisoner of Conscience'' signs and even
brought flowers to greet her as she left the federal prison on
Monday. But Kathleen Rumpf, a New Yorker and a roaming protester
for left-wing causes, never showed up. On the day of her scheduled
release from the Federal Medical Center, Carswell, where she served
a year for spray-painting a sign outside a controversial U.S. Army
post in Georgia, Rumpf started another protest _ she is refusing to
promise to pay her $2,000 fine, imposed when the judge sent her to
prison. EDS: Will be updated with any spot developments. By CHRIS
VAUGHN. Story will move in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
