<TEXT>
<P>
   BILL-LANN-LEE (Washington) _ Bill Lann Lee, the acting head of
the Justice Department's civil rights division, says he hopes the
Senate will confirm him in the post so that he would have more
clout in dealing with government agencies. Republican senators
opposed Lee when he came up for confirmation two years ago because
of his support for affirmative action. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
