<HEADER>
A7283 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TRIVIAQ&AMP;A-TEX     07-20 0458
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIAQ&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NOW, THIS IS A BIG STRETCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service Clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find pants stretchers? _ C.T., Cleburne
</P>
<P>
   A: They're available in the current catalog of the Vermont
Country Store.
</P>
<P>
   Pants stretchers are wire contraptions that are placed inside
damp pants as they are drying to crease the pants and prevent
wrinkles. They also may be sold in some independent hardware stores
and country stores.
</P>
<P>
   The Vermont Country Store includes pants stretchers in its
Summer 1999 ``Voice of the Mountains'' catalog. A large pair sells
for $14.95 as item No. 26082, and a small pair sells for $13.95 as
item No. 30105.
</P>
<P>
   To order or request a free catalog, call (802) 362-8440 or visit
the World Wide Web site www.vermontcountrystore.com. You also can
write to the company at Box 3000, Manchester Center, VT 05255-3000.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Tony Goldwyn, the voice of Disney's new
``Tarzan?'' _ G.F., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to him in care of Creative Artists Agency, 9830
Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   Goldwyn is a grandson of the ``G'' in Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer _
Samuel Goldwyn, the pioneering film producer who co-founded
companies that became Paramount Pictures and MGM Studios. His
parents are producer Samuel Goldwyn Jr. and actress Jennifer
Howard.
</P>
<P>
   The 39-year-old actor made his directing debut this year with
``A Walk on the Moon'' and has two more directorial assignments
upcoming. ``Tarzan'' was one of the first projects his 4 and
9-year-old daughters are allowed to see in full. They never made it
to the end of his first major film role, 1990's ``Ghost.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I had to turn it off because it was near the end of the movie
and I was about to get axed,'' he told the Toronto Sun. ``When
they're 12, 13 years old, maybe.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Who wrote ``The Hunchback of Notre-Dame,'' and what was the
history behind the author? _ M.D.H., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: ``The Hunchback of Notre-Dame'' is the English title of
``Notre-Dame de Paris,'' a French novel written in 1831 by Victor
Hugo.
</P>
<P>
   Hugo, who lived from 1802 to 1885, was already one of France's
most successful poets and playwrights at the time ``Notre-Dame''
was published. He wrote the book to fulfill an 1828 contract for a
historical novel, finishing it more than two years past deadline.
</P>
<P>
   ``Victor Hugo: A Biography,'' a recent book by Graham Robb, was
published in paperback last month.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-20-99 1711EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
