<P>
   TECHNOLOGY-LIMITS _ ATLANTA _ Following a study by Bell Labs,
the buzz in many technology circles has been over the ``limits'' on
future development of microchips. Scientists now see research
approaching limitations on increased miniaturization of chips given
the material now used. James Meindl, who heads chip development at
Georgia Tech, says there's a problem but it won't restrict R&AMP;D
within the next 10 years, and beyond that point there is a solution
already on the horizon: Deployment of tantalum oxides instead of
silicon oxides. Hello, Tantalum Valley. (Holsendolph, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CCE-EARNINGS _ ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola Enterprises took a $103
million charge, or 16 cents a share, for its recall of products in
Europe in the second quarter, giving it net income of $33 million,
or 8 cents a share. Excluding the charge, profit was 24 cents a
share, higher than expected. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   NETBANK-EARNINGS _ ATLANTA _ Atlanta-based Net.B(at)nk released
quarterly earnings figures Tuesday as well as updated deposit and
account numbers. Security First network bank also released numbers
recently. A look at Atlanta's Internet banks and their growth.
(Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HOMEWIRELESS _ ATLANTA _ Atlanta-based Home Wireless Networks,
Inc., has been trying mightily since 1996 to market its technology,
which is an inexpensive package of gizmos that will allow home or
business users to use one phone line to set up a network that
includes computers, printers, faxes and telephone linked
wirelessly. Now Lucent has invested and the regional phone
companies are studying the product and ultimately may market it.
This kind of support can turn a garage business into a
billion-dollar cash cow. (Holsendolph, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MP3 _ MP3.com prepares its IPO this week as the recording
industry gathers in New York City attempting to get a better grasp
on this runaway new medium that has the potential to change
consumer buying habits and record company policies and pracitces
that have been in place for years. The consensus is that old media
must work with the new technologies and find some kind of middle
ground. Everyone agrees it has to be done, but no one is sure how.
</P>
<P>
   Cox's investment in MP3.com could be an attempt to build that
bridge and establish an early toe-hold in an Internet sector ready
to explode. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EQUIFAX _ ATLANTA _ Equifax announces earnings and an Internet
marketing deal with Lycos. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AFC-COFFEE _ AFC Enterprises will locate 167 Seattle's Best
coffee stores in Japan. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ Both large and small investors need appropriate
asset allocation. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 18. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the current week. This
layout is now available.)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0717: 1999 CHEVROLET IMPALA _ For the Chevrolet
faithful, the Impala name has a long and storied history, and the
2000 model won't embarrass them or its predecessors. (DeVault,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes 3-column color photo of
car's exterior and an 6-pica color photo of car's interior.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 1999 Chevrolet
Impala.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SHARP DRIVING _ Saturn is about to join the midsize
bandwagon, dominated by three of the best-selling cars in America,
with its new L (for ``larger'') series. (Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). Includes 1-column color photograph of
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ Like a lot of other folks, I used the Fourth of
July weekend to do some traveling. I enjoy people watching. They
put on a much better show than most television programs or movies.
Perhaps my most important observation came in the area of seat belt
usage. Make no mistake about it, I think only dummies don't use
them. (Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ Locating the right shop to fix your particular
vehicle's emmissions problem is going to require a little sleuthing
on your part. (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) 16. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE _ Inside and outside, the '99 Isuzu VehiCross is an
eye-catcher that illustrates the diversity and exclusivity that
have come to the sport-utility market. (DeVault, Cox News Service)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DRUG-PROFITS _ To compete with national pharmacy chains,
community corner drugstores are clinging to their clientele by
tapping into new markets. A Gonzalez drugstore draws out-of-town
customers by selling specially flavored children's medication. But
the big chains aren't the worst enemy, according to pharmacists _
insurance companies are really pinching the profit margins. (Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
