<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of July 21, 1999, and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   TEJON-DEVELOPMENT (Los Angeles) _ Tejon Ranch, long the home of
cattle pastures and steep roads, may soon see strip malls and
housings tracts. The Tejon Ranch Co. announced Tuesday that it has
signed a letter of intent with three homebuilders to develop a
4,000-acre master-planned community. By Jason Takenouchi. (Will
move in the ``f'' financial news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-PRODUCTION (Los Angeles) _ Now it's getting personal.
Canada's ambassabor to the United States has sent a letter to
Congressman Howard Berman, D-Mission Hills, complaining that the
Valley representative is unfairly bashing Canada for hosting
Hollywood productions. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f''
financial news files.)
</P>
<P>
   HOTEL-CENTER (Lancaster, Calif.) _ Starwood Hotels and Resorts
will establish a reservation center in Lancaster, selecting the
city over 160 others for the 250-job operation, officials announced
Tuesday. Starwood, which includes the Sheraton and Westin Hotel
chains, plans to establish a regional reservation center at a
former La-Z-Boy furniture showroom. By Jim Skeen. (Will move in the
``f'' financial news files.)
</P>
