ADOPTION (Phoenix) - A Phoenix family is adopting 10 siblings,
ranging in age from 4 to 17. This is the largest single adoption
all from one family in Arizona, possibly the nation, DES officials
say. The children are half Native American; the parents are white.
They originally had several of the children as foster kids and met
the siblings through visits. The decided that the children should
be together; adoption is final July 23. By KARINA BLAND. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
