MOMENTS (Phoenix) - You may not believe this now, but last
weekend's crash that killed JFK jr., his wife and her sister,
probably is not a `where were you when` moment. In fact, it's
getting harder to come by those moments, because any story almost
immediately begets 24-hour media coverage. Still, though, there are
exceptions, and they change by generation. The end of World War II;
Pearl Harbor. Kennedy's assassination. The explosion of the
Challenger. The moon landing. Even the O.J. Simpson slow-speed
Bronco chase. Princess Diana. What does it take to make those
moments? By BOB GOLFEN. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
