Y2K-readiness expense increased operating costs at America West
Airlines in the second quarter but the carrier managed record
earnings of $554.2 million. That is a 6.8 percent increase over the
second quarter of 1998 for Tempe-based America West and the best
quarterly earnings in company history, according to Doug Parker,
executive president. By PETER CORBETT. Story will move in the ``F''
category. &QL; 
