<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-POOL-FUN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
10 HOT PLAYTHINGS FOR COOL POOL FUN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service Clients) 
By ALYSON WARD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Heat's up, pool's cool, but a kid can swim from one side to the
other only so many times before boredom sets in.
</P>
<P>
   We surveyed the local public pools recently and found most
children finding distraction with the same old standbys _ foam
noodles and power water guns and floating cushions. Not bad, but we
knew it could get better. So we went shopping.
</P>
<P>
   Here, our suggestions for the hottest new water toys under the
sun:
</P>
<P>
   1. Dive rings
</P>
<P>
   For 20 years, dive sticks ruled the pool for throw-and-go-seek
play. Last month, though, about 19 million of the sinking sticks
were recalled after several children were impaled by the 4- to
8-inch sticks.
</P>
<P>
   The alternative? Dive ``rings,'' weighted plastic loops kids can
seek and find without risk of injury. Most sets have various point
values marked on the individual rings, so you can challenge
competitors by tossing the higher-point rings into the deepest
parts of the pool.
</P>
<P>
   Made by several companies, including Aqua Games and Aqua Fun;
$7-$11.
</P>
<P>
   2. Splash Bombs
</P>
<P>
   These inexpensive soft balls are about the size of softballs,
but they behave more like sponges. Let 'em soak up water, and
they'll squish and splash when you throw them. A good choice for
backyard fun _ all you need is a hose or a bucket of cold water.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Primetime Toys International; about $2.
</P>
<P>
   3. The Original Toypedo
</P>
<P>
   This rubbery torpedo toy glides through the water when you throw
it. It can even pick up speed as it moves, and it'll go as far as
40 feet.
</P>
<P>
   Toypedo games are also available, including the Toypedo
Pop-A-Ring Target Game. Hit the underwater targets with the
Toypedo, and they'll float to the surface.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Swim Ways; $17-$21.
</P>
<P>
   4. Hologram goggles
</P>
<P>
   Create the illusion: Holograms built into these goggles cover
your eyes with piranhas or sharks, flies or skulls or lightning
bolts. Some pairs even give you reptilian eyes.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Speedo; $5-$10.
</P>
<P>
   5. Skip Disk
</P>
<P>
   Throw this spongy Frisbee-type disc to play catch while you're
in the pool. It's designed not to sink but to skip across the
water.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Swim Ways; About $10.
</P>
<P>
   6. Bumper Jumper and Paddle Pumper
</P>
<P>
   Floats are notorious for flipping over and dumping you off. But
not this one. Straddle the upright, ride-designed Bumper Jumper and
you'll stay on, even if you're in the middle of battle. Propel
yourself with the Paddle Pumper, a paddle with a water blaster at
the other end for serious combat.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Short Stack; About $10.
</P>
<P>
   7. ``Star Wars: Episode I'' pool floats
</P>
<P>
   A good mix of summer fun and shameless marketing. Float around
with your favorite characters from ``The Phantom Menace:'' the
Jar-Jar two-person ride-in, the Millennium Falcon Island/River
Raft, Anakin's Podracer pool lounger.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Intex; $10-$15.
</P>
<P>
   8. Scuba Scope
</P>
<P>
   The Scuba Scope works like a periscope; you can swim with this
face mask and still see above water.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Short Stack; About $13.
</P>
<P>
   9. Vortex Mega Howler
</P>
<P>
   This foam football's tail makes it spiral in the air, so it can
go farther than other foam footballs, maybe up to 100 yards.
Whistles on the sides make noise as it flies _ hence the name Mega
Howler. Appropriate for play in or out of the water.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Oddzon; About $10.
</P>
<P>
   10. Splash Volleyball set
</P>
<P>
   Get a team together and spike an inflatable ball over a floating
net. Kids who've tried it say you need at least four or five people
to really have fun with this one.
</P>
<P>
   Made by Swimline; About $20.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
