<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SLAYINGS-TEXAS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AUTHORITIES SEEK MOTIVE AFTER TEENS SUSPECTED OF KILLING COUPLE
FOUND DEAD 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By KATHY WALT 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Authorities were still trying to determine
Tuesday what prompted a 16-year-old boy and his 13-year-old buddy
to apparently kill the older teens' parents, then drive to a remote
area where they both either committed suicide or died in a
murder-suicide.
</P>
<P>
   The bodies of Mark Miller, 49, and his wife, Linda ``Katy''
Miller, 42, were found Sunday in the Miller's home in southeast
Austin, near the Austin-Bergstrom International Airport.
</P>
<P>
   The next day, the bodies of the Millers' 16-year-old son, Shawn,
and their 13-year-old next-door neighbor, Gerald Davis, were
discovered about 50 miles away in neighboring Bastrop County. Both
apparently had been dead since some time Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   ``The only thing we have seen is that perhaps we had a situation
of obviously a troubled young man in Shawn Miller,'' said Travis
County Sheriff Margo Frasier. ``Nothing that we have uncovered
would justify or lead to this kind of action.''
</P>
<P>
   Frasier said authorities do not know whether Shawn Miller killed
Davis and then himself or whether both boys committed suicide, but
they believe Davis was shot first.
</P>
<P>
   The Travis County Medical Examiner's office also had not issued
a ruling on the manner of deaths by Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   Both boys suffered close-range gunshot wounds to the head. A
.410-gauge shotgun was found on Miller's body and is consistent
with one of the weapons used in murders of Miller's parents, said
Frasier.
</P>
<P>
   A note found on Shawn Miller's body expressed remorse, but
Frasier declined to disclose what it said. She said authorities
have not verified that Shawn wrote the note and don't know whether
both teen-agers were involved in the slaying of Miller's parents.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have no reason to suspect that anyone else was involved''
in the elder Millers' slayings, she said.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities believe the elder Millers were killed Sunday morning
after returning home from church. The parents died of multiple
gunshot wounds from a .410 shotgun and a .22-caliber firearm. Mark
Miller was shot in the back and his wife in the abdomen.
</P>
<P>
   Frasier said the boys then took the Miller family's 1989 Volvo
station wagon. It was later found stuck along a rural road in
Bastrop County. Inside were Mrs. Miller's purse, some coins and a
backpack similar to those a lot of teen-agers carry, Frasier said.
</P>
<P>
   ``My personal opinion is (the boys) didn't know where they were
going or what they were going to do,'' the sheriff said.
</P>
<P>
   Frasier said authorities are trying to determine where the boys
got the shotgun found on Shawn Miller, although ``it's a pretty
common type gun that people might keep in their homes.''
</P>
<P>
   Frasier also said neither of the boys had been in trouble with
law enforcement, but that Shawn Miller ``was not the best at
socializing.'' However, he had no history of psychological or
psychiatric treatment, she said.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
