<P>
   &UR; LATINAS AND SOCCER &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Although Latinos usually are huge soccer fans, the Los Angeles
Times reports that there were relatively few Latino fans for the
Women's World Cup.
</P>
<P>
   The newspaper also notes that there were few competitors from
South American countries, except for Brazil. Half the players on
the Mexican team were Mexican Americans.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's machismo,'' Los Angeles sports commentator  &UR; Manolo &LR; 
 &UR; Cevallos &LR;  said. Latinos ``do not want women to step out of their
feminine role _ the home, children, housework _ because it
challenges the masculine role. The countries that performed the
best (in the World Cup) are countries where women have a greater
role in public life and society _ and so, of course, in soccer.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
