<P>
   KENNEDY-COMMENTARY (Undated) _ Moments after early reports of
John F. Kennedy Jr.'s missing single-engine plane hit the
television airwaves, I began getting telephone calls from friends,
relatives and former colleagues. They all knew that I had commuted
on summer weekends from New York City to Martha's Vineyard,
piloting a single-engine airplane, for the past seven years. They
wanted my ``take'' on what might have happened to Kennedy.
</P>
<P>
   By Lee J. Guittar. (Story will move in the ``k'' category.)
