   (NYT15) BOYNTON BEACH, Fla. -- July 20, 1999 -- CUBA-EXODUS,
07-20 -- Ray Dieppa, 37, originally of San Jose de las Lajas, Cuba,
came to the United States in May, 1980 during the exodus of Cubans
which became known as the Mariel Boatlift. In the heaviest exodus
since Fidel Castro allowed 33,000 people to exit the island in
1994, more than 1,500 Cubans have made it ashore in South Florida
so far this year. But increasingly, say U.S. Coast Guard officials,
the Cubans are making their passage not on rafts or in fishing
vessels but in the boats of smugglers who bring them in close
enough to swim ashore or launch a small dinghy. (Andrew Itkoff/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
