presented by the Labyrinth Theater Company and Center Stage, N.Y.
``In Arabia'' is an old-fashioned slice-of-life play that takes
place around Times Square before Walt Disney replaced Damon Runyon
as resident folklorist, and it involves a collection of modern-day
losers that even Runyon might find hard to stomach. (Norman Y.
Lono/New York Times Photo)
