brief suborbital flight on July 21, 1961, is lifted out of the
ocean some 90 miles northeast of Great Abaco Island in the Bahamas,
early Tuesday. The recovery took place on the 30th anniversary of
mankind's first moon landing. The space capsule had been missing
since it sank 10 minutes after splashdown on July 21, 1961, nearly
drowning Grissom. (The Discovery Channel/New York Times Photo) Eds:
Credit Manditory.
